        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 10:59PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 1059 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles south of Weldona, or 9 miles west of Fort Morgan, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fort Morgan, Log Lane Village and Adena School.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
